      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "COMPTON GOLD (7) is a fast beginner who appreciated the inside draw with an all the way win (30.35) at Angle Park in Grade 5 over 530m. Form here sound including five wins. Form from her last run is proving to be solid. Looks to have an edge on most of these. NITROUS (1) broke a string of placings finishing in the money two on end before a last start eighth (43.98) at Angle Park. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. Has ability and can measure up. CROCODILE ROLL (3) was safely held in tougher company last start at this track, but prior to that won comfortably by 4.5 lengths at this track (29.88) beating Take The Steps in a Special conditions race on April 24. Should be thereabouts. BANDIT DARYL (5) continues to race well and is sure to be competitive again.",
